The paper introduces a new model of interactive proofs and explores its connections to quantum complexity theory, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.QA (Quantum Algebra) likely categories. The paper also discusses algorithms and approximation for dense CSPs, which are related to topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper uses subsampling techniques, which are often studied in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
